<style>
  /* ============================================================
   * HairMNL CSS overrides — Pipeline 8 port (M3)
   *
   * Ported 2026-05-17 from Pipeline 6's snippets/css-overrides.liquid.
   * Most rules carry over without selector changes — Judge.me / Klaviyo /
   * LoyaltyLion / Nova GDPR / BOGOS / Reamaze classes are all
   * vendor-managed and theme-independent.
   *
   * Selectors that target Pipeline 6's own DOM (.header__desktop,
   * .footer__title, .product__slides, .product__pickup, .product__price__wrap,
   * .announcement__wrapper, .media__thumb__wrapper, .blog__article__content,
   * header.theme__header, .section-recent.recent__container, .pb_image_wrapper,
   * .points-box) are flagged inline with `P8-VERIFY:` comments. These need
   * confirmation against the Pipeline 8 dev theme DOM during Phase 5 visual QA;
   * Pipeline 8 may have renamed classes that would make these rules no-ops
   * (harmless but useless).
   *
   * One block deliberately dropped vs the P6 version: #pwa-modal display:none
   * for Shop Sheriff PWA. That app has been uninstalled since 2026-05-01,
   * so the modal element no longer renders. Block removed; saves ~10 LoC
   * and avoids carrying dead code to P8.
   *
   * kt0 lint compliance: this file MUST pass `python3 scripts/check-overlay-css.py`
   * before merge. All `contain: layout` uses on overlay-class selectors carry
   * `kt0-OK:` justifications inline.
   * ============================================================
   */

  /* P8-VERIFY: .header__desktop / .header__mobile are P6 header classes.
     If P8 uses different classes (e.g. .Header__desktop, [data-section-type="header"]),
     these rules become inert — Phase 5 QA confirms or re-targets. */
  .header__desktop {
    height: 70px;
  }

  .header__mobile {
    height: 60px;
  }

  /* A11y fix 2026-04-28 — footer accordion triggers were <p> with
     aria-controls/aria-haspopup/aria-expanded, which Lighthouse flagged
     as 'aria-allowed-attr' violation (those ARIA attrs require <button>
     or <a>). Changed sections/footer.liquid to <button type="button">.
     This rule resets browser button defaults so .footer__title still
     looks like the previous <p> styling: full-width text-aligned-left,
     transparent background, no border (the .footer__title rule already
     defines border-bottom), no extra padding from button defaults,
     inherits font from parent. */
  button.footer__title {
    background: transparent;
    border: none;
    border-radius: 0;
    padding: 0 0 10px;
    margin: 0 0 20px;
    text-align: left;
    width: 100%;
    font: inherit;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: inherit;
    cursor: pointer;
    display: block;
    font-weight: var(---font-weight-accent-bold);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }
  button.footer__title:focus { outline: 2px solid var(--secondary); outline-offset: 2px; }

  /* CLS fix 2026-04-28 — Judge.me 'Verified by' logo image is rendered
     by app HTML without explicit width/height attributes. PSI flagged
     it as "Media element lacking an explicit size" causing layout
     shifts where the .jdgm-medals-wrapper appears (PDP footer +
     /reviews page). Reserving the rendered dimensions (125x24 per
     Lighthouse boundingRect) prevents the shift. Aspect ratio also
     declared so width: 100% containers compute height correctly. */
  .jdgm-verified-by__image {
    display: inline-block;
    width: 125px;
    height: 24px;
  }
  .jdgm-verified-by__image img {
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    display: block;
    aspect-ratio: 125 / 24;
  }

  /* CLS fix 2026-04-29 — Blog article body images come from Shopify's
     rich-text editor, which doesn't add width/height attributes. Without
     dimensions, browsers can't reserve space → image loads → all content
     below shifts down → catastrophic CLS.

     Real-shopper RUM data (GA4 web-vitals last 7 days) showed 4 of the
     top 5 worst CLS pages were blog posts:
       /blogs/hair-education/rebonding-vs-keratin-treatment   54.9% poor
       /blogs/product-spotlight/lockdown-lab-purple-shampoos  51.9% poor
       /blogs/product-spotlight/15-top-sulfate-free-shampoos  49.2% poor (n=392)
       /blogs/tousled-online-magazine/how-to-hide-gray-hair   47.1% poor

     Fix strategy:
     1. `aspect-ratio: auto 16 / 9` — when intrinsic ratio is unknown
        (image hasn't loaded yet), fall back to 16:9 (most blog photos
        are landscape). When intrinsic ratio becomes available, browser
        switches to it. This pre-reserves vertical space at first paint.
     2. `width: 100%` paired with the aspect-ratio so the browser can
        compute height upfront from container width.
     3. `height: auto` ensures intrinsic ratio wins once image loads,
        even if intrinsic differs from 16:9.
     4. `max-width: 100%` prevents oversized images overflowing.
     5. `display: block` prevents baseline-aligned shifts from inline imgs.
     6. Background placeholder color so the reserved area is visible
        instead of empty white.

     Selector targets `.blog__article__content` (full article page) and
     all `.rte` content (blog list/preview cards too). Limited to images
     that DON'T already have width+height attrs (skips already-sized
     images so the rule doesn't accidentally regress them).

     Caveat: portrait images will appear as 16:9 first then snap to
     their portrait ratio when loaded — still better than 0px → full
     height jump. For perfect fix, would need server-side image
     dimension parsing in Liquid (article.content is HTML string, no
     direct Image objects). Acceptable trade-off given the 49–55% poor
     baseline. */
  .blog__article__content img,
  .rte img {
    max-width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    display: block;
  }
  .blog__article__content img:not([width]):not([height]),
  .rte img:not([width]):not([height]) {
    aspect-ratio: auto 16 / 9;
    width: 100%;
    background: #f4f6f8;
  }

  /* CLS fix 2026-05-13 hairmnl-theme-987 — Blog article body iframe/video embeds.
     Shopify article rich-text content often includes <iframe> embeds (YouTube,
     Vimeo) and <video> elements that render with no explicit dimensions or
     aspect-ratio. These collapse to 0×0 then expand to full video height when
     loaded, shifting all content below them in .blog__article__content (and
     .rte on pages). This rule reserves a 16:9 box so the layout is stable
     before the embed loads. */
  .blog__article__content iframe,
  .blog__article__content video,
  .rte iframe,
  .rte video {
    aspect-ratio: 16 / 9;
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    display: block;
    background: #f4f6f8;
  }

  /* CLS fix 2026-05-10 hairmnl-theme-ojx — Pro Blogger related-articles thumbnails.
     snippets/pro-blogger.snippet.related-item.liquid renders <img> without
     width/height attrs (lines 5 + 20); image URLs use Shopify CDN
     ?height=400 query param so they're 400px tall but variable width.
     Without dimensions, each thumbnail shifts content as it loads —
     6+ thumbnails per blog post = CLS 0.52 on
     hair-education/purple-vs-blue-shampoo-philippines (POOR bucket, GSC
     5/10). Existing article-content-with-img-dims snippet doesn't
     recognize ?height= query params, only _WxH.ext patterns.

     Reserve 1:1 aspect-ratio (matches typical thumbnail container style
     per .pb_image_wrapper) so browser allocates space before image loads.
     width:100% lets the image fill its parent. height:auto + object-fit:
     cover preserves visual fit when actual image aspect differs from 1:1.
     background reserves a visible placeholder color during load. */
  .pb_image_wrapper img:not([width]):not([height]) {
    aspect-ratio: 1 / 1;
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    display: block;
    background: #f4f6f8;
    object-fit: cover;
  }

  /* Same pattern for .responsive-wide-image which also renders unsized
     in some article contexts (cross-post-blogs widget). 16:9 fallback
     matches the existing .blog__article__content rule at line 138-143. */
  .responsive-wide-image:not([width]):not([height]) {
    aspect-ratio: auto 16 / 9;
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    display: block;
    background: #f4f6f8;
  }

  /* CLS fix 2026-04-29 (updated 2026-05-18 hairmnl-theme-gso0) — Judge.me
     medals wrapper starts as `.jdgm-hidden` (display: none) in the initial
     HTML and gets revealed by Judge.me's loader.js once badges hydrate.
     The reveal grows the wrapper from the reserved size to its rendered
     height, pushing all in-flow content below it down → CLS.

     Real-shopper RUM showed /products/wella-professionals-koleston-
     perfect-ppd-free 49.1% poor CLS (n=116 events). Wella PDP image
     gallery is dimensioned correctly (width=1180 height=1180), so the
     remaining CLS source is the medals wrapper appearing post-load.
     Same pattern affects EVERY page since the widget renders at the top
     of sections/footer.liquid.

     2026-05-18 gso0 update — measured actual rendered heights via Chrome
     DevTools on https://www.hairmnl.com/ (jdgm-medals-wrapper has
     flex-wrap behavior that varies dramatically by viewport width):
       - viewport ≥ 768px: 133px (verified-wrapper + separator + 5 medals
         all on one row)
       - viewport <  768px: 411px (children wrap to 3 stacked rows on
         mobile because verified-wrapper 200px + separator + medals 320px
         won't fit in 412px viewport)
     The previous 80px reservation was correct for 5-medals-in-a-row
     desktop but undersized the mobile case by ~331px. PSI 2026-05-18
     attributed 0.185 cumulative CLS to #shopify-section-footer shifts
     from this widget — fully explained by the 80→411 reveal on mobile.

     Fix: while .jdgm-hidden is applied, override display to block but
     keep visibility: hidden so the element occupies its eventual height
     without showing content. Mobile-first min-height matches the wrapped
     layout; desktop breakpoint drops to single-row height. contain: layout
     prevents residual size variance from cascading to siblings. When
     Judge.me removes .jdgm-hidden, the badges become visible in the same
     reserved space — no shift.

     Caveat: if Judge.me's JS gates hydration on display: none → display:
     block transition, this override could break their logic. Loader.js
     v490 (audited 2026-04-27 per beads memory) gates on
     .jdgm-preview-badge presence, not display state, so the override
     should be safe. Revert this rule if medals stop appearing. */
  .jdgm-medals-wrapper.jdgm-hidden {
    display: block !important;
    visibility: hidden !important;
    min-height: 411px;
    contain: layout;
  }
  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .jdgm-medals-wrapper.jdgm-hidden {
      min-height: 134px;
    }
  }

  /* CLS fix 2026-05-10 hairmnl-theme-z9y — Judge.me preview badge top-of-PDP shift.
     <div class="jdgm-widget jdgm-prev-badge"> renders empty at PDP top
     below product title; loader.js injects stars + "N reviews" → grows
     from 0 → ~24px → top-of-page shift → 884 URLs failing CLS on
     kerastase-blond-absolu PDP grouping. Reserve typical badge height
     so the hydration is paint-only, not layout. contain:layout
     isolates internal star-count changes from cascading. */
  .jdgm-widget.jdgm-prev-badge {
    display: inline-block;
    min-height: 24px;
    min-width: 100px;
    contain: layout;
  }

  /* CLS fix 2026-05-01 T2 / 2026-05-02 1pi update / 2026-05-13 hod (987 Phase 2) — Cart page:
     #freegifts-main-page-container. Initial T2 fix reserved 80px (one gift
     row). 1pi increased to 160px (2 rows). hod increased to 240px (3 rows) after
     GA4 showed 84 cart__template wrapper shifts — 160px still overflowed when
     active offers showed 3+ gift rows. The blank gap when fewer/no gifts are
     active is the accepted trade-off. contain:layout unchanged. */
  #freegifts-main-page-container {
    min-height: 240px;
    contain: layout;
  }

  /* CLS fix 2026-05-01 T8 — PDP Flickity media thumbs:
     div.media__thumb__wrapper.flickity-enabled.is-draggable is the GA4
     debug_target for 36 poor-CLS events in 7d on PDP pages. Before Flickity
     initializes, the wrapper has no explicit height — its height comes from
     the inline-block .media__thumb items (each 60px + 15px vertical margins
     = ~75px rendered). When Flickity fires, it restructures the wrapper DOM
     and briefly collapses the strip before re-measuring.

     Fix: set min-height on the wrapper to the typical rendered height
     (80px = 60px thumb + 10px top margin + 5px bottom margin + 5px buffer).
     contain:layout prevents internal Flickity reflows from cascading.
     overflow:hidden prevents any overflow during Flickity's brief transition. */
   .media__thumb__wrapper {
     min-height: 80px;
     contain: layout;
     overflow: hidden;
   }

  /* CLS fix 2026-05-18 T27 — PDP Flickity thumb items inside media__thumb__wrapper:
      The wrapper-level fix (T8 above) set min-height + contain:layout on the
      wrapper, but CLS persists (0.205, box 542×73). Root cause: before Flickity
      initializes, .media__thumb items are inline-block flow children that
      define the wrapper's intrinsic height. When Flickity fires, it wraps them
      in .flickity-slider (position:absolute) inside .flickity-viewport — the
      thumbs are removed from flow and the wrapper height briefly collapses
      before the viewport inherits from the parent. The wrapper contain:layout
      already isolates, but the individual thumbs still shift from inline-block
      flow to absolute-positioned Flickity cells.

      Fix: stabilize each .media__thumb with explicit dimensions matching the
      base theme.css values (width:60px, height:60px) and force them to remain
      inline-block regardless of Flickity class mutations. Also set explicit
      width/height on the child img and aspect-ratio:1 as a fallback, so the
      img cannot collapse if it loads after Flickity restructures the DOM. */
  [data-product-thumbs] .media__thumb {
    display: inline-block;
    width: 60px;
    min-width: 60px;
    height: 60px;
    min-height: 60px;
  }
  [data-product-thumbs] .media__thumb img {
    display: block;
    width: 60px;
    height: 60px;
    aspect-ratio: 1;
  }

  /* CLS fix 2026-05-01 T9 — Header CLS:
     GA4 debug_target theme__header recorded 88 poor-CLS events in 7d.
     Two causes:

     1. Announcement bar: the ticker JS (announcement__scale ticker--unloaded
        → loaded) and the Flickity slider init both fire after DOM parse,
        potentially causing the .announcement__wrapper height to briefly
        change. The announcement section renders before the header in DOM;
        any height change there can affect the absolute-positioned header's
        visual position at the top of the page.

     2. LoyaltyLion .points-box: for logged-in users, two data-lion-points
        spans inside .header__desktop start empty then get injected with the
        points balance by LoyaltyLion's SDK. The injection can cause the
        account navlink to reflow internally.

     Fix 1: min-height on .announcement__wrapper prevents the bar from
     collapsing to 0 during ticker initialization. 36px is the typical
     rendered height of a single-line announcement bar (font-size ~14px
     + ~22px vertical padding from .announcement__bar).

     Fix 2: .points-box gets height: 0 / overflow: hidden for logged-out
     users (no .is-loggedin → spans never get display:block from theme.css
     line 15667). For logged-in users it stays block. contain:layout on
     .points-box prevents the injection from reflowing sibling nav items. */
  .announcement__wrapper {
    min-height: 36px;
  }

  .points-box {
    contain: layout;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  /* CLS fix 2026-05-13 hairmnl-theme-7i0 — Announcement bar ticker height lock.
     Custom JS Ticker class (theme.dev.js Bar constructor) removes
     ticker--unloaded after DOMContentLoaded. During that window, font FOUT
     causes text reflow within max-content width, shifting the ticker frame
     height. Pinning height + overflow:hidden prevents any vertical shift.
     white-space:nowrap enforces single-line (announcement is line-height
     constrained). No contain:layout — pure dimension pinning is kt0-safe. */
  .announcement__wrapper [data-ticker-frame] {
    height: 24px;
    overflow: hidden;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }

  /* CLS fix 2026-05-10 kt0 — Desktop header element shift:
     GA4 RUM (last 14d, deviceCategory=desktop) shows header.theme__header
     contributing 165 poor-CLS events + 52 on the parent #shopify-section-header
     = 14.4% of all desktop CLS. The May 2 sprint fixed the announcement bar
     and .points-box internal reflow, but shifts inside the header itself
     (logo paint, cart count hydration, LoyaltyLion data-lion-points injection)
     still cascade to the header's outer dimensions, which the rest of the page
     reacts to.

     Fix: `contain: layout` on the header element isolates internal mutations
     from affecting siblings. No min-height because typical rendered heights
     differ across breakpoints (mobile ~50px, desktop ~80px) and we'd risk
     inflating one or under-reserving the other. Combined with the existing
     .points-box contain:layout (mobile fix May 2), this gives two-level
     isolation for the LoyaltyLion injection case.

     Mobile already has CLS p75 = 0.07 (GOOD), so this fix is desktop-targeting
     but global — contain:layout is safe on either breakpoint.

     2026-05-11 HOTFIX — REMOVED .header__wrapper from this selector.
     The cart-drawer ({% render 'cart-drawer' %} at sections/header.liquid:334)
     is rendered AFTER `</header>` (line 330) but INSIDE `.header__wrapper`
     (closes at line 338). `contain: layout` establishes a containing block
     for fixed/absolute descendants per CSS Containment spec — that trapped
     the drawer's `position: fixed; z-index: 20050` inside `.header__wrapper`'s
     bounds instead of overlaying the viewport. Result: opening the cart drawer
     on a PDP rendered the drawer panel inline within the header area while
     PDP content showed alongside (perceived as "drawer rendering behind
     elements"). User-reported live regression.

     `header.theme__header` alone is safe — the drawer renders OUTSIDE the
     `<header>` element (after its closing tag at line 330), so containment
     here doesn't establish a containing block for the drawer. CLS GA4
     attribution was on `header.theme__header` (165 events) + parent
     `#shopify-section-header` (52 events) — `.header__wrapper` was a
     speculative addition, never showed in field data, and removing it loses
     nothing on CLS. */
  header.theme__header {
    contain: layout;
  }

  /* CLS fix 2026-05-01 e4a-α — PDP store availability widget:
     .product__pickup contains [data-store-availability-container], an empty
     div in the Liquid that Zapiet's app embed populates with store pickup
     availability after JS loads. The div grows 0px → ~60px when Zapiet
     fires, shifting the footer and any below-fold content. Same injection
     pattern as #freegifts-main-page-container (fixed earlier today).

     Fix: reserve 64px (typical height of a single store row: store name
     ~20px + status ~20px + 4px gap + 20px vertical padding). contain:layout
     isolates internal Zapiet DOM mutations from cascading to siblings.
     The gap when no stores match the variant is an acceptable white-space
     trade-off vs. a layout shift on every PDP pageload. */
  .product__pickup {
    min-height: 64px;
    contain: layout;
  }

  /* CLS fix 2026-05-01 e4a-β — PDP Flickity main gallery height animation:
     .product__slides .flickity-viewport has `transition: height 0.4s` in
     theme.css line 14885. This animated height transition fires whenever
     Flickity adjusts viewport height — including during init on pages where
     the first-slide aspect-ratio and --default-ratio match (so net shift is
     0), the 400ms animation still triggers continuous layout recalc that
     browsers can record as micro-shifts.

     Fix: override the transition to `none` for the main product gallery only.
     The thumbnail strip (.media__thumb__wrapper) already has contain:layout
     (T8 fix) and doesn't need this. Disabling the transition means height
     changes snap immediately — one discrete event rather than 400ms of
     animated shifts. The visual experience is unchanged because the aspect-
     ratio pre-reservation (--default-ratio inline style on .product__slides)
     means the viewport should not need to change height at all on init for
     most products. */
  .product__slides .flickity-viewport {
    transition: none !important;
  }

  /* CLS fix 2026-05-01 7fz — Reamaze chat widget label.
     2026-05-12 narrowed: the original rule used [id^="reamaze-widget"] which
     applied position:fixed + contain:layout to ALL Reamaze widget elements.
     contain:layout on the outer #reamaze-widget container created a new
     containing block for Reamaze's absolute-positioned children (per kt0
     rule in CLAUDE.md), pushing the icon to right:-58px and container to
     bottom:-16914.5px — visually breaking the chat widget. Narrowed to the
     label element only (which is the actual CLS culprit). position:fixed
     alone already takes the label out of flow; contain:layout is redundant
     for CLS purposes and risks the same kt0 issue on a future re-render. */
  #reamaze-widget-label {
    position: fixed !important;
  }

  /* CLS fix 2026-05-02 fan — PDP product price column:
     GA4 debug_target div.grid__item.medium-up--one-half logged 251 poor-CLS
     events/7d across all PDPs (Wella all-shades worst at 44 events, 52% poor).

     Original root cause (now resolved at the source 2026-05-13): the
     bss-b2b-product-vat snippet inlined a <style> that hid
     .shopify-section .product__price with display:none before BSS B2B JS
     revealed the correct price. This collapsed .product__price__wrap from
     its rendered height (~44px) to 0, then BSS set display:block → the
     price area re-expanded → shifted variant selector, ATC button, and
     content below. BSS B2B Solution was uninstalled 2026-05-13 (bd dyp,
     commit 1c0da46), removing that snippet, so the BSS-induced collapse
     no longer occurs.

     This rule is retained as a defensive reservation. If any future
     vendor app injects a similar hide-then-reveal price pattern, the
     min-height absorbs the shift without re-investigation. contain:layout
     also isolates internal price changes (sale badges, strikethrough
     compare-at price) from cascading to siblings. The 44px reservation
     is invisible in the common case (price renders immediately at ≥44px
     height); only matters if a future widget hides the price column. */
  .product__price__wrap {
    min-height: 44px;
    contain: layout;
  }

  /* CLS fix 2026-05-02 1pi-b — Cart page recently-viewed section:
     sections/section-recent-products.liquid renders with style="display:none"
     on the products container. JS populates from localStorage then removes
     display:none. Section grows from 0 → ~360px (6 product cards × ~60px
     row height) pushing site footer down. Footer is below-fold so CLS impact
     is low, but still recorded in GA4. Reserve 300px (minimum 4 products ×
     ~75px each) to prevent the grow-from-zero shift. */
  .section-recent.recent__container {
    min-height: 300px;
    contain: layout;
  }

  /* CLS fix 2026-05-02 e4a-γ — Klaviyo body-injected signup modal:
     PSI filmstrip frame 8 on serioxyl PDP shows the Klaviyo signup modal
     appearing mid-load and pushing PDP content. Klaviyo's runtime CSS
     sets the modal to position:fixed once their stylesheet hydrates, but
     between when the modal HTML is appended to <body> and when their CSS
     loads, the modal briefly occupies document flow as a body child →
     shifts every in-flow sibling below it.

     Confirmed safe: `grep -rn "klaviyo-form" sections/ snippets/` returns
     zero inline embeds — Klaviyo at HairMNL is exclusively the body-level
     modal popup injected by the Klaviyo Shopify App Embed. The selector
     uses `body > ...` so any future inline form embedded inside a section
     container is unaffected. Forcing position:fixed in our <head> CSS
     wins because <head> parses before Klaviyo's loader script downloads.

     Class patterns covered:
     - `klaviyo-form-*` — Klaviyo's standard modal form ID class
     - `kl-private-reset-css-*` — Klaviyo's css-reset wrapper (random suffix)
     - `[data-testid^="klaviyo-form"]` — newer Klaviyo SDK builds

     Caveat: this rule will break any Klaviyo embed form rendered as a
     direct <body> child (atypical — embeds normally live inside section
     containers). Revert if signup CTAs stop appearing inline anywhere. */
  body > [class*="klaviyo-form"],
  body > div[class*="kl-private-reset-css"],
  body > [data-testid^="klaviyo-form"] {
    position: fixed !important;
    z-index: 9999 !important;
    contain: layout !important;
  }

  /* CLS fix 2026-05-02 e4a-δ — LoyaltyLion body-injected notification/popup:
     LoyaltyLion's "Sign up for HairMNL Rewards to get a Php100 voucher"
     notification bar and any LL overlay popup are injected as direct body
     children by their SDK loader (sdk.loyaltylion.net/static/2/loader.js,
     dns-prefetched at theme.liquid:87). Same lifecycle gap as Klaviyo —
     SDK appends the notification HTML before its own stylesheet sets
     position:fixed, so it briefly renders in flow.

     Selector targets only body-level descendants:
     - `[id^="lion-"]` — LL's standard ID prefix on overlay/notification els
     - `[class*="ll-notification"]` / `[class*="ll-popup"]` — LL legacy markup
     - `[class*="lion-overlay"]` — LL modal backdrop

     The `.lion-points-box` element is NOT body-level (it lives inside
     .header__desktop nav, theme.liquid header section), so `body > ...`
     scoping naturally excludes it — the T9 header CLS fix at
     css-overrides.liquid:235 handles that one in-flow.

     Caveat: any future LL embed widget rendered as direct body child
     (atypical for LL — they place inline widgets via merchant-supplied
     containers like `<div data-loyaltylion></div>`) would break. */
  body > [id^="lion-"],
  body > [class*="ll-notification"],
  body > [class*="ll-popup"],
  body > [class*="lion-overlay"] {
    /* kt0-OK: scoped to `body > *` so it only matches LoyaltyLion's
       top-level body-injected popup containers (not arbitrary children).
       LL popups have no absolutely-positioned descendants that need to
       escape the popup boundary (icon/close button are inside the popup
       flow). Verified shipping cleanly since 2026-05-02 e4a-delta. */
    position: fixed !important;
    contain: layout !important;
  }

  /* CLS fix 2026-05-04 0u4 — Booster EU Cookie Bar / Nova GDPR cookie banner:
     The Nova EU Cookie Bar GDPR app embed (settings_data.json: nova-eu-cookie-bar-gdpr,
     confirmed active) uses the cookieconsent library which:
     1. Injects inline <style> into <head> at runtime via createElement
     2. Creates .cc-window.cc-banner DOM (position:fixed in its own CSS)
