  /* CLS fix 2026-05-04 3uw — BOGOS/Secomapp Free Gifts gift image + notification containers.

     DOM structure confirmed from live page source:
       <div id="freegifts-main-popup-container" class="freegifts-main-container sca-modal-fg"
            data-animation="slideInOutTop"></div>
       <div id="sca-fg-notifications" class="sca-fg-notifications"></div>

     These divs are injected into <body> as empty elements during initial HTML parse.
     BOGOS JS later populates them with content (images, promotion bars).
     The BOGOS inline CSS block — including #sca-gift-thumbnail .sca-gift-image — is
     also injected at JS runtime, creating a lifecycle gap where:
     1. Div exists in document flow (empty but in flow)
     2. JS fires → injects content → size jumps from 0 → full height
     3. BOGOS CSS block loads → applies position (too late)
     = layout shift on PDP.

     Fix A: .sca-gift-image — pre-declare 160×160 from our <head> CSS so the browser
     reserves space before BOGOS's own CSS lands. Dimensions confirmed from BOGOS's own
     inline CSS: "#sca-gift-thumbnail .sca-gift-image { width: 160px; max-height: 160px; }".
     aspect-ratio: 1/1 + object-fit: cover ensures images that are slightly non-square
     still fit without causing height instability.

     Fix B: Force the notification and modal containers to position:fixed + contain:layout
     before they receive content. Our <head> CSS wins the race against BOGOS's runtime
     injection — same mechanism as e4a-γ (Klaviyo) and e4a-δ (LoyaltyLion) fixes.

     Caveat: #sca-promotion-glider (also present in BOGOS inline CSS) may still shift
     content if it renders inline. Monitor GA4 CLS attribution for this selector. */
  .sca-gift-image {
    width: 160px;
    height: 160px;
    aspect-ratio: 1 / 1;
    object-fit: cover;
  }

  #freegifts-main-popup-container,
  #sca-fg-notifications {
    position: fixed !important;
    contain: layout !important;
  }

